2 courgette
1 fresh chilli  (optional)
1 Onion
1 cup white wine vinegar
3 tbs sugar
1 tbs salt
1 cup water
1 sachet Curry Powder

• Thinly slice courgette into rounds. Thinly slice chilli and onion.
• Transfer veggies to a large sterilized jar.

TIP: Slicing the veggies very thinly helps them pickle faster!

• To a medium saucepan, add the white wine vinegar, sugar, salt and water
to a medium saucepan over high heat.
• Bring to the boil over high heat and cook until sugar is dissolved,
1-2 minutes. Remove saucepan from heat and add curry powder, stirring
to combine.

• Pour pickling liquid into pickle jar until veggies are covered. Top up with
more boiling water if necessary.
• Seal with a lid and allow to cool. Store in the fridge until ready to eat,
3-4 hours or overnight.
TIP: The pickles are best enjoyed the next day!

• Serve sweet and spiced courgette pickles from fridge as desired. Enjoy!